Egypt Stocks: Alexandria Portland Cement, EFG-Hermes Holding

-- B y   A h m e d   A   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-03-30T13:03:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/egypt-stocks-alexandria-portland-cement-efg-hermes-holding.html
Egypt ’s benchmark  EGX 30 Index (EGX30) 
gained for a fourth day, gained 1.3 percent to 5,480.94 at the
1:30 p.m. close in Cairo. The measure has retreated 23 percent
this quarter, the world’s worst performer.  The following stocks rose or fell in Egypt. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Alexandria Portland Cement Co. (ALEX EY) rose 4.2 percent
to 17.95 Egyptian pounds, the highest since Jan. 17. The
nation’s third-biggest publicly traded cement manufacturer said
profit increased 17 percent to 590 million pounds ($99 million)
last year.  EFG-Hermes Holding SAE (HRHO EY) advanced 2.8 percent, the
most since Jan. 4, to 21.75 pounds. Egypt’s biggest publicly
traded investment bank said profit increased 27 percent to 700.8
million pounds in 2010.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
